  "prompt": "How can you see if someone deleted you on LINE?",
  "response": "On LINE, like many other messaging apps, there's no direct way to see if someone has deleted or blocked you. However, there are a few signs you could look for that might indicate that you've been deleted:\n\n1. **Messages Not Delivered**: If you send messages to the person and they are never marked as \"Read,\" even after a significant amount of time, it might mean you\u2019ve been blocked or deleted. \n\n2. **Profile Information**: If you can no longer see the person\u2019s profile picture or status messages, it could be because they've removed you, though it could also be due to their account settings.\n\n3. **Timeline Posts**: If you were previously able to see their timeline posts and now you can\u2019t see any new posts, or all posts have disappeared, it may be a sign that you\u2019ve been deleted or they\u2019ve changed their privacy settings.\n\n4. **Group Chats**: If you share a group chat and the person\u2019s messages are not delivered to you within the group, it could indicate that you\u2019ve been blocked.\n\n5. **Stickers**: If you can no longer send LINE stickers to the person, this can be another indicator that the person may have deleted or blocked you.\n\nNote that these signs are not conclusive, as changes in privacy settings or other actions taken by the other user can also result in similar behavior. LINE does not explicitly notify you if someone deletes or blocks you for privacy reasons.",
